==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[wicca#Old English|wiċċa]] {{m}}, [[wicce|wiċċe]] {{f}}.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: wĭch
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /wɪʧ/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /wItS/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪtʃ|-ɪtʃ]]

====Homophones====
*[[which]] {{italbrac|depends on accent}}

===Noun===
'''witch''' (plural: '''witches''')

# A (usually female) person who uses [[magic]].
# {{italbrac|derogatory}} An ugly or unpleasant woman.
#: ''I hate that '''old witch'''.''

